description:
&lt;p&gt;Following an establishment review, Whitchurch Community Hospital is looking to recruit a full time Healthcare Assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Hospital is seeking a Healthcare Assistant that is flexible and has transferable skills. They will have a passion for rehabilitation and palliative care and the ability to work as part of a team and individually within the Inpatient ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a vital role within the team supporting our patients with personal, medical and rehabilitation needs. This will involve supporting trained nurses, therapist, medical staff and ward co-ordinators in care planning, evaluation and discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So if you are willing to go the extra mile to make patients feel important then we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All posts include a commitment to work: days, nights, weekends, and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 25th to 26th November 2020 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit please contact: Nikki Ryder, Ward Manager on 01948 666292.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
